verses.text_plain: In the year that king Uzziah died I saw also the Lord sitting upon a throne, high and lifted up, and his train filled the temple.
verses.verse_html:
1In the year that king Uzziah died I saw also the Lord sitting upon a throne, high and lifted up, and his train filled the temple. ▼
▼ his…: or, the skirts thereof

footnotes.body_html: ▼ his…: or, the skirts thereof

verses.text_plain: Above it stood the seraphims: each one had six wings; with twain he covered his face, and with twain he covered his feet, and with twain he did fly.
verses.verse_html: 2Above it stood the seraphims: each one had six wings; with twain he covered his face, and with twain he covered his feet, and with twain he did fly.

verses.text_plain: And one cried unto another, and said, Holy, holy, holy, is the Lord of hosts: the whole earth is full of his glory.
verses.verse_html:
3And one cried unto another, and said, Holy, holy, holy, is the Lord of hosts: the whole earth is full of his glory. ▼
▼ one…: Heb. this cried to this
 , ▼
▼ the whole…: Heb. his glory is the fulness of the whole earth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ one…: Heb. this cried to this
footnotes.body_html: ▼ one…: Heb. this cried to this

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the whole…: Heb. his glory is the fulness of the whole earth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the whole…: Heb. his glory is the fulness of the whole earth

verses.text_plain: And the posts of the door moved at the voice of him that cried, and the house was filled with smoke.
verses.verse_html:
4And the posts of the door moved at the voice of him that cried, and the house was filled with smoke. ▼
▼ door: Heb. thresholds

verses.text_plain: Then said I, Woe is me! for I am undone; because I am a man of unclean lips, and I dwell in the midst of a people of unclean lips: for mine eyes have seen the King, the Lord of hosts.
verses.verse_html:
5Then said I, Woe is me! for I am undone; because I am a man of unclean lips, and I dwell in the midst of a people of unclean lips: for mine eyes have seen the King, the Lord of hosts. ▼
▼ undone: Heb. cut off

footnotes.body_html: ▼ undone: Heb. cut off

verses.text_plain: Then flew one of the seraphims unto me, having a live coal in his hand, which he had taken with the tongs from off the altar:
verses.verse_html:
6Then flew one of the seraphims unto me, having a live coal in his hand, which he had taken with the tongs from off the altar: ▼
▼ having…: Heb. and in his hand a live coal

tokens.text: unto me, having a live coal

footnotes.body_text: ▼ having…: Heb. and in his hand a live coal
footnotes.body_html: ▼ having…: Heb. and in his hand a live coal

verses.text_plain: And he laid it upon my mouth, and said, Lo, this hath touched thy lips; and thine iniquity is taken away, and thy sin purged.
verses.verse_html:
7And he laid it upon my mouth, and said, Lo, this hath touched thy lips; and thine iniquity is taken away, and thy sin purged. ▼
▼ laid…: Heb. caused it to touch

footnotes.body_text: ▼ laid…: Heb. caused it to touch
footnotes.body_html: ▼ laid…: Heb. caused it to touch

verses.text_plain: Also I heard the voice of the Lord, saying, Whom shall I send, and who will go for us? Then said I, Here am I; send me.
verses.verse_html:
8Also I heard the voice of the Lord, saying, Whom shall I send, and who will go for us? Then said I, Here am I; send me. ▼
▼ Here…: Heb. behold me

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Here…: Heb. behold me

verses.text_plain: And he said, Go, and tell this people, Hear ye indeed, but understand not; and see ye indeed, but perceive not.
verses.verse_html:
9And he said, Go, and tell this people, Hear ye indeed, but understand not; and see ye indeed, but perceive not. ▼
▼ indeed, but understand: or, without ceasing, etc: Heb. in hearing, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ indeed, but understand: or, without ceasing, etc: Heb. in hearing, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ indeed, but understand: or, without ceasing, etc: Heb. in hearing, etc

verses.text_plain: Make the heart of this people fat, and make their ears heavy, and shut their eyes; lest they see with their eyes, and hear with their ears, and understand with their heart, and convert, and be healed.
verses.verse_html: 10Make the heart of this people fat, and make their ears heavy, and shut their eyes; lest they see with their eyes, and hear with their ears, and understand with their heart, and convert, and be healed.

verses.text_plain: Then said I, Lord, how long? And he answered, Until the cities be wasted without inhabitant, and the houses without man, and the land be utterly desolate,
verses.verse_html:
11Then said I, Lord, how long? And he answered, Until the cities be wasted without inhabitant, and the houses without man, and the land be utterly desolate, ▼
▼ utterly…: Heb. desolate with desolation

footnotes.body_html: ▼ utterly…: Heb. desolate with desolation

verses.text_plain: And the Lord have removed men far away, and there be a great forsaking in the midst of the land.
verses.verse_html: 12And the Lord have removed men far away, and there be a great forsaking in the midst of the land.

verses.text_plain: But yet in it shall be a tenth, and it shall return, and shall be eaten: as a teil tree, and as an oak, whose substance is in them, when they cast their leaves: so the holy seed shall be the substance thereof.
verses.verse_html:
13But yet in it shall be a tenth, and it shall return, and shall be eaten: as a teil tree, and as an oak, whose substance is in them, when they cast their leaves: so the holy seed shall be the substance thereof. ▼
▼ and it…: or, when it is returned, and hath been broused
 , ▼
▼ substance: or, stock, or, stem
